OL,3,CStudent hopes to become first ever
OL,4,CDeafblind person to climb Mount Everest
OL,6,FITV Granada Reports Merseyside
OL,7,FCorrespondent Andy Bonner went to meet
OL,8,FCaroline and hear about her challenge
OL,10,FA student is enjoying her last few
OL,11,Fdays of relaxation before taking on a
OL,12,FNew Year's resolution like no other -
OL,13,Ftraining to become the first ever deaf
OL,14,Fand blind person to climb to the top
OL,15,Fof Mount Everest.
OL,17,FCaroline Pakenaite, 29, has Usher
OL,18,Fsyndrome, a rare genetic condition
OL,19,Fwhich affects her sight, hearing and
OL,20,Fbalance.
