OL,3,CStudent hopes to become first ever
OL,4,CDeafblind person to climb Mount Everest
OL,6,FThe condition means she has night
OL,7,Fblindness, and with her tunnel vision
OL,8,Fnarrowing she says she knew she wanted
OL,9,Fto see more of the world before her
OL,10,Fsight disappears entirely.
OL,12,FBut it was not until she was on a trek
OL,13,Fto Everest base camp that Caroline,
OL,14,Ffrom Southport, realised no DeafBlind
OL,15,Fperson had ever reached the summit.
OL,17,F"I wanted to claim that fact," she
OL,18,Fsaid. "I also realised I have a story
OL,19,Fto tell. I want to bring a better
OL,20,Funderstanding about what blind means,
OL,21,Fwhat Deafblind means.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
