OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F399A1735475965
OL,3,CStudent hopes to become first ever
OL,4,CDeafblind person to climb Mount Everest
OL,6,F"I still wasn't really believing that
OL,7,FI would go blind. But this year, it
OL,8,Fmade me realise it's about time. Time
OL,9,Fis limited."
OL,11,FCaroline first noticed her vision
OL,12,Fdeteriorating aged just 19, and after
OL,13,Fa series of appointments was finally
OL,14,Fdiagnosed with Usher.
OL,16,F"I always had very good sight, very
OL,17,Fgood sight, but I started to wear
OL,18,Fglasses at age 13," she said.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
