OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F399A1735475965
OL,3,CStudent hopes to become first ever
OL,4,CDeafblind person to climb Mount Everest
OL,6,F"So, I still want to go on, I want to
OL,7,Fsee the world as much as possible so
OL,8,Fif and when I lose my sight, I'll have
OL,9,Fthe most amazing memory. I'll feel
OL,10,Flike I'll be ok."
OL,12,FChallenges completed by Caroline so
OL,13,Ffar include running the London
OL,14,FMarathon and climbing the highest
OL,15,Fpeaks in England, Scotland, and Wales
OL,16,Fin 24 hours.
OL,18,FShe has also just become the first
OL,19,Fdeafblind woman to scale the 6,476-
OL,20,Fmetre Mera Peak in the Himalayas.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/6
